Fix it? The Browser has a template. Copy it. Code f.e.: browser_ajax < plugin.tx_browser_pi1.javascript.ajax.jQuery.default. The typeNum has to be %typeNum%. Alternate: don't use AJAX.

Fix it? Configure the general storage pid. See tab [Behaviour] field [Record Storage Page]. Bear in mind to set more than one pid, if your data are stored in more than one folder.
Fix it: include the Static Template "Browser"!

If you get an unexpected result nevertheless, you can enable the DRS - the Development Reporting System. You will get a report with all rendered SQL queries among others. You enable the DRS in the extension manager.
Fix it: Save the Flexform once.
